org.beryx.streamplify.benchmark

Class DelayedBenchmark

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.beryx.streamplify.benchmark.DelayedBenchmark

  • public class DelayedBenchmark
extends java.lang.Object
    This benchmark shows that in situations where the iterator's next() method is time consuming, the IteratorSpliterator created by Spliterators.spliterator(Iterator, long, int) is not adequate for parallel processing, and the LongIndexedSpliterator should be used instead.

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Compares the performance of the implementation using LongIndexedSpliterator with that of the IteratorSpliterator created by Spliterators.spliterator(Iterator, long, int).
        On multicore and multiprocessor systems, the implementation based on LongIndexedSpliterator is typically faster.
